**Abstract:**
A humanities grant progress report (Sections A-1 and A-2). The document reports on summer research conducted at the Centre Culturel "Les Fontaines" at Chantilly, France, collecting material from medieval sources. The author states the project goal was to establish that medieval objections to adopting the Aristotelian scientific model can be legitimately couched in terms of speech acts and narrative theory. Reports that the material collection was completed by June 10, and substantive drafts of two papers are underway.

**AI Recommendation:** Administrative document showing project planning and progress; useful for understanding the author's research methodology and timeline.

